The substation, which is a distribution unit, was struck by lightning at the weekend and affected three transformers. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom  on Tuesday said it had restored power to more than 5,000 customers after a fire damaged a substation in Balfour, Mpumalanga. The substation, which is a distribution unit, was struck by lightning at the weekend  and affected three transformers. The power utility said two of the three transformers were shut down as a safety measure and they were in the process of being replaced. Eskom spokesperson Dikatso Mothae said: “The first transformers burned out completely and we are in the process of replacing it. Transformer three was tested and found to be safe to be switched back on. And in terms of the second transformer, tests are continuing and we are optimistic it will be repaired.”